'''Josimar José Évora Dias''' ({{IPA|pt|ʒɔ.zi.ˈmaɾ ʒu.ˈzɛ ˈɛ.vu.ɾɐ ˈdi.ɐʃ|lang}}; born 3 June 1986), known as '''Vozinha''' ({{IPA|kea|vɔ.ˈzi.ɲɐ|lang}}), is a Cape Verdean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

He played for clubs in his country, Angola, Moldova, Portugal and Cyprus. A full international with over 50 [[cap (sport)|caps]] for [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] since 2012, he played at the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] in [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations|2013]], [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations|2015]], [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]] and [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]]

==Club career==
Born in [[Mindelo]] on the island of [[São Vicente, Cape Verde]], Vozinha began his career at local [[Batuque FC]], playing for them until 2011 before moving to local city rivals [[CS Mindelense]]. Following good showings with the club, he was signed by [[Progresso Associação do Sambizanga]] in Angola. He returned to Mindelense in 2013 and played in the [[São Vicente Island League]].{{citation needed|date=August 2023}}

After a year at [[FC Zimbru Chișinău|Zimbru Chișinău]] in Moldova, Vozinha moved in August 2016 to [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] of the [[Liga Portugal 2|Portuguese second tier]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Vozinha no Gil Vicente de Portugal|trans-title=Vozinha to Portugal's Gil Vicente |url=https://expressodasilhas.cv/desporto/2016/08/05/vozinha-no-gil-vicente-de-portugal/49684 |access-date=24 November 2021 |work=[[Expresso das Ilhas]] |date=5 August 2016 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

==International career==
Vozinha made his debut for [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] on 8 September 2012 in a [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations]] [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|playoff]] first leg at home to [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]], a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cabo Verde vence Camarões por 2 -0 com sabor a pouco|trans-title=Cape Verde defeat Cameroon 2-0 with little flavour|url=https://noticiasdonorte.publ.cv/4815/cabo-verde-vence-camaroes-por-2-0-com-sabor-a-pouco/ |access-date=24 November 2021 |publisher=Notícias do Norte |date=8 September 2012 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He remained in goal for the second leg in [[Yaoundé]] on 14 October, a 2–1 loss that saw his country qualify for their first major tournament.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cabo Verde pela primeira vez na CAN|trans-title=Cape Verde in the ACN for the first time|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-internacional/cabo-verde-pela-primeira-vez-na-can_d595140 |access-date=24 November 2021 |publisher=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal]] |date=14 October 2012 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> At the finals in South Africa, the team reached the quarter-finals before a 2–0 loss to [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]]; he conceded the second goal after going up the pitch in the dying seconds to attack a [[corner kick]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ghana 2-0 Cape Verde |url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2013/0202/365920-ghana-make-last-four-in-acn/ |access-date=24 November 2021 |publisher=[[Raidió Teilifís Éireann]] |date=2 February 2013 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

Vozinha also played at the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Vozinha: "Entramos em campo sempre para ganhar"|trans-title=Vozinha: "We always go out on the pitch to win"|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/can/detalhe/vozinha-entramos-em-campo-sempre-para-ganhar-926674 |access-date=24 November 2021 |work=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |date=21 January 2015 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> On 7 October 2020, he earned his 50th cap in a 2–1 [[exhibition game|friendly]] win away to [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Seleção de Cabo Verde: Vozinha completou 50 jogos pela seleção nacional |trans-title=Cape Verde national team: Vozinha completed 50 games for the national team |url=https://gaftsports.com/selecao-de-cabo-verde-vozinha-completou-50-jogos-pela-selecao-nacional/ |access-date=24 November 2021 |publisher=Gaft Sports |date=12 October 2020 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=24 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124204050/https://gaftsports.com/selecao-de-cabo-verde-vozinha-completou-50-jogos-pela-selecao-nacional/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> and a year later he was called up for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Cameroon.<ref>{{cite news |title=Afcon 2021: Ethiopia and Cape Verde squads for finals in Cameroon where he was sent off in the round of 16 vs Senegal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/59763245 |access-date=24 December 2021 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=23 December 2021}}</ref> Vozinha was called up to play at the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] for Cape Verde.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://fcf.cv/can-2023-os-26-convocados/| title= CAN 2023: Os 26 convocados|date=28 December 2023}}</ref>

==Personal life==
His younger brother [[Delmiro]] was also a Cape Verde international.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=SAPO|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/girabola/artigo/2014/01/29/progresso-contrata-delmiro-irmao-de-vozinha|title=Progresso contrata Delmiro, irmão de Vozinha|trans-title=Progresso hire Delmiro, brother of Vozinha|date=29 January 2014|language=pt}}</ref>

